    "title": "What is Misconduct?",
    "displayTitle": "What is Misconduct?",
    "body": "<p>As an employee of the Government of Canada, we all must follow the Departmental Code of Conduct. In this document, there are rules for how we are to behave on a daily basis while carrying out our duties. When we contravene these rules, it could be considered as misconduct. Other organizations have similar rules by which their employees must abide. Let us take a look at how misconduct is defined for Integrity investigation purposes.</p>",
